{
  "texts": [
    "The Fit4-Function approach directly tackles this problem by leveraging a moderately sized, all viable, low-bias (ML-designed) library to generate highly reproducible data for multi-trait learning with a low false positive rate.",
    "This allows the models to be applied in different combinations with a low risk of aggregating significant error.",
    "MultiFunction libraries can thus be generated to more efficiently explore the vast sequence space for multi-trait capsids.",
    "The Fit4Function approach can help to reduce the need for extensive screening in animals.",
    "Firstly, the distinct features of Fit4-Function libraries enable the quantitative assessment of capsid biodistribution and candidate selection from just a single round of screening."
  ]
}